description: Sample Windows Forms app using the ThermalLabel Editor Add-on. It features visual aids for the creation of items like texts, barcodes, RFID, pictures and shapes; an undo/redo engine, Grid-lines, snap to grid, Cut-Copy-Paste functionality, Z-ordering, zooming, keyboard shortcuts for well-known common actions, In-place text edition for TextItem objects and many more features! It is also very customizable so you can skin it to match the appâ€™s UI style on which it will be hosted in. With the ThermalLabel Editor component, you can allow your end-users to create, load, edit and save ThermalLabel objects in the form of XML template file definition or .NET object within your own .NET apps. You can also export the labels to PDF or raster image formats by leveraging the ThermalLabel SDK ThermalLabel Editor provides First-Class Internationl Barcode Standards compliance. Neodynamic is an expert in the barcode field and all the barcode algorithms were written from ground up based on the official specifications. ThermalLabel Editor leverages the ThermalLabel SDK and provides you and your end-users with barcode generation for most popular Linear (1D), Postal & 2D Symbologies/Standards including Code 39, Code 128, GS1-128 (formerly EAN/UCC-128), GS1 DataBar (RSS-14),  EAN 13 & UPC, Postal (USPS, British Royal Mail, Australia Post, DHL, etc.), Data Matrix (including GS1 version), QR Code, PDF 417, UPS MaxiCode, Micro QR Code, ALL EAN/UPC Composite Barcodes (CC-A, CC-B & CC-C), Chinese Han Xin Code, IFA PPN, Postmatrix and many more!
summary: Sample Windows Forms C# app using the Visual ThermalLabel Editor component to create a professional barcode label designer for your end users.
title: Visual ThermalLabel Editor for .NET - Windows Forms C# Sample
